Lucien Callamand https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucien_Callamand 0 Lucien Callamand born Lucien Marie Pascal Eugène Callamand (April 1, 1888, in Marseille – December 3, 1968, in Nice, Alpes-Maritimes) was one of the earliest French film actors whose career transcended 6 decades of French cinema. He starred in 115 films between 1909 and 1965.
